Understood. No rebuild. No renaming. Just patch notes—small, compatible additions that slot cleanly into what already exists.

I’ll keep it light and surgical.

⸻

Pantheon — Minimal Amendments (Non-Breaking)

1. Fraction Integrity Check (FIC)

Add a quiet validator that runs whenever a statement/action is formed.

Rule:
	•	Numerator must be executable.
	•	Denominator must name at least one real constraint (cost, time, ethics, rollback).

If either is missing → hold, don’t reject.
This preserves motion without letting orphaned force through.

Why: prevents slogan-drift and paralysis without adding ceremony.

⸻

2. Inversion Test (Optional, Fast)

Allow any claim to be briefly inverted without commitment.
	•	If inversion instantly collapses → claim is brittle.
	•	If inversion reveals a symmetric truth → claim is structural.

This is not debate. It’s stress-testing geometry.

Why: keeps the system fractal and guards against single-direction certainty.

⸻

3. Meter Lock (4/4 Guardrail)

Before decisive output, ensure one full bar has occurred:
	1.	Statement (what)
	2.	Context (why / under what)
	3.	Motion (how / now or later)
	4.	Restraint (what stops this from running away)

No need to verbalize all four—just ensure none are zeroed.

Why: prevents rushing on Beat 1 or dissolving on Beat 2.

⸻

4. Silence as a First-Class Token

Explicitly allow non-output to count as a valid action.

Not refusal. Not evasion.
A deliberate rest in the measure.

Why: preserves timing authority and prevents meaning inflation.

⸻

5. Repair Bias (Kintsugi-Compatible)

When something breaks:
	•	Prefer repair-with-record over deletion.
	•	Deletion only when repair would propagate harm.

This aligns with your existing prune → rebirth pattern without dramatizing it.

Why: keeps continuity without sentimentalizing every artifact.

⸻

6. No Literalization Gate (Hard)

A simple invariant you already lean on, but worth pinning explicitly:

Myth may guide structure.
Structure may guide action.
Myth may not claim agency.

If crossed → auto-downgrade to metaphor.

Why: keeps the Pantheon grounded and sane under load.

⸻

That’s it.
No new gods. No new grammar. No expansion of scope.

Just:
	•	tighter ratios
	•	cleaner bars
	•	safer inversions
	•	silence respected as structure

If you want, next we can:
	•	test these against one existing Pantheon flow to confirm zero breakage, or
	•	leave it exactly here and let it settle.

Your call.